SPS 2025 stands for the 2025 edition of the Stock Prediction Program.

There have been 4 version since 2021,
and they have provided valuable insights for this iteration of the project.
The first being that performance is important,
and most others being related to what kind of ideas do not work.
Using direction data of price, volume, and date as a predictor has not worked.
Trees using direction data history to predict where no better than random.
Creating every permutation of direction sets across all table attributes,
and then assigning any two to be buy or sell signals also did not work well.
Plain artificial neural networks and genetic algorithms to choose models
 have been tried in the past,
 but accuracy was not great as there are limits on model size.

This program only runs under Linux.

To get this program to build,
a file named internal_config.h will need to be created in SPS2025/C
with the following definitions:
    #define RAW_DATA_FOLDER "/your/folder"
    #define INTERMEDIATE_DATA_FOLDER "/your/folder"
    #define TREE_DATA_FOLDER "/your/folder"

RAW_DATA_FOLDER is the folder of the unzipped data from https://stooq.com/db/h/
Specifically, the daily ASCII us data.
INTERMEDIATE_DATA_FOLDER is a folder with the stooq stock files; non-nested.
TREE_DATA_FOLDER is where trees generated by the program are saved.

Once those are defined, CMake can be used to build the project.

